<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-669] Scripts should specify bash instead of /bin/sh</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-669</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Ken Williams said:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Just out of interest, I also reckon your &apos;build-cluster-syntheticcontrol.sh&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
script should be a bash script (#!/bin/bash) rather than a standard&lt;br/&gt;
shell (#!/bin/sh) script.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;$ trunk/examples/bin/build-cluster-syntheticcontrol.sh&lt;br/&gt;
trunk/examples/bin/build-cluster-syntheticcontrol.sh: 28: Syntax error: &quot;(&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
unexpected (expecting &quot;fi&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
$&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
