                            <comment id="13019736" author="kenwilliams" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 09:56:34 +0100"  >
&lt;p&gt;Patch changes &apos;examples/bin/build-cluster-syntheticcontrol.sh&apos; from being a standard shell script to a bash shell script. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve not converted any of the other shell scripts at the moment because I&apos;ve not had a chance to check them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ken&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019739" author="kenwilliams" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 09:59:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a patch file - how do I actually commit it ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ken&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019745" author="ssc" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 10:15:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;just attach the patch file here (best to name it &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-669&quot; title=&quot;Scripts should specify bash instead of /bin/sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.patch), someone with commit access will review it and commit it afterwards&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019750" author="kenwilliams" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 10:33:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I see, I click &apos;More Actions&apos;, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks lots,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ken&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019831" author="hudson" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 14:48:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #747 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/747/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/747/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-669&quot; title=&quot;Scripts should specify bash instead of /bin/sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; script must have a bash shebang&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020151" author="lancenorskog" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2011 02:25:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;One &quot;standard&quot; is &lt;br/&gt;
#!/usr/bin/env bash&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This walks through the incoming path and finds the first &apos;bash&apos; program. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shebang_(Unix)#Portability&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shebang_(Unix)#Portability&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, Amazon Map/Reduce does not support it, even though it&apos;s Posix:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://forums.aws.amazon.com/thread.jspa?threadID=60007&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://forums.aws.amazon.com/thread.jspa?threadID=60007&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
